{"Body":"<p>Not sure if that counts as BCTs but in my native speaker's intuition there are three basic words for 'blue' in Polish: </p>\n\n<ul>\n<li><em>granatowy</em> 'navy blue, dark blue'</li>\n<li><em>błękitny</em> 'azure, light blue'</li>\n<li><em>niebieski</em> 'blue'</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>I will admit that in my poor, CGA 16-colour world of a male, <em>niebieski</em> is an umbrella term for all three. For my wife, however, they are seperate colours — even if <em>pink</em> and <em>salmon</em> are, too.</p>\n", "Id":"1501", "ParentId":"1025", "LastEditorUserId":"794", "CreationDate":"2012-02-26T19:09:36.490", "OwnerUserId":"794", "PostTypeId":"2", "comments":[], "LastEditDate":"2012-02-26T21:16:07.107", "LastEditedUser":{"UpVotes":"46", "WebsiteUrl":"http://www2.filg.uj.edu.pl/ifo/kjasis/~stachowski.kamil", "Location":"Cracow, Poland", "Id":"794", "DownVotes":"2", "AccountId":"414249", "Views":"49", "Reputation":"1128", "CreationDate":"2012-02-24T07:50:20.713", "DisplayName":"kamil-s", "LastAccessDate":"2013-12-23T10:10:41.103", "AboutMe":""}, "LastActivityDate":"2012-02-26T21:16:07.107", "Score":"2", "CommentCount":"4", "OwnerUser":{"UpVotes":"46", "WebsiteUrl":"http://www2.filg.uj.edu.pl/ifo/kjasis/~stachowski.kamil", "Location":"Cracow, Poland", "Id":"794", "DownVotes":"2", "AccountId":"414249", "Views":"49", "Reputation":"1128", "CreationDate":"2012-02-24T07:50:20.713", "DisplayName":"kamil-s", "LastAccessDate":"2013-12-23T10:10:41.103", "AboutMe":""}}